  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Presents to the Emergency Department (ED) and meets the clinical definition for Acute
             Bacterial Skin and Skin Structure Infections (ABSSSI)

          -  Known or suspected gram-positive infection.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Known or suspected gram-negative infections, anaerobic infections, or fungemia

          -  Known or suspected infections that are severe, life threatening or are not included in
             the ABSSSI Food and Drug Administration (FDA) guidance

          -  Injection drug users with a fever

          -  Severe neurological disorder leading to immobility or confined to a wheelchair

          -  Bilateral Lower extremity involvement of the suspected infection.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
    <gender>All</gender>
    <minimum_age>18 Years</minimum_age>
    <maximum_age>N/A</maximum_age>
